description:
Create a violation test for the `no-skip-tests` rule in `config/semgrep/no-skip-tests.yml`.

## Rule being tested
Forbids `#[ignore]` attribute on tests. Pattern regex: `#\[ignore\]`. No path restrictions.

## What to create
**Directory:** `violations/rust/no-skip-tests/`
**File:** `violations/rust/no-skip-tests/src/lib.rs`

## Violation code
```rust
//! Test Rust CLI application
#![warn(missing_docs)]

use thiserror::Error;

/// Application-specific errors.
#[derive(Error, Debug)]
pub enum AppError {
    /// An unexpected error occurred.
    #[error("unexpected error: {0}")]
    Unexpected(String),
}

/// Run the application.
///
/// # Errors
///
/// Returns an error if the application fails to execute.
pub fn run() -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    println!("Hello from test-rust-project!");
    Ok(())
}

#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;

    #[test]
    fn test_run_succeeds() {
        assert!(run().is_ok());
    }

    #[test]
    #[ignore]
    fn test_ignored() {
        panic!("should not run");
    }
}
```

## What it asserts
Running `just code-semgrep` must **fail** because `#[ignore]` matches the regex pattern.

